25|$|A <b>heliograph</b> was {{installed}} in 1879 at Signal Hill, the small rise overlooking the main settlement in Thomson Bay. A Frenchman {{by the name of}} Henri Courderot was the <b>heliograph</b> operator and was paid $10 per year to operate the service once a day weather permitting.|$|E
